  "text": "of Xue et al. [CITATION_1] , text are considered to be enclosed by 4 segments, i.e. a pair of long-side borders (abdomen and back) and a pair of short-side borders (head and tail). The method of Xue et al. is also the first to use DenseNet [CITATION_2] as their basenet, which provides a consistant 2 − 4% performance boost in F1-score over that with ResNet [CITATION_3] on all datasets that it's evaluated on.",
